com.symbian.commdb.data
Class TableEntry

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.symbian.commdb.data.TableEntry
public class TableEntry
extends java.lang.Object

This class represents a particular entry of a CommDB table and it contains all the values for the parameters of this entry. Note that a table entry depends on the definition of a table template (TableTemplate class) and therefore an instance can only be created when a table template instance has been created and supplied as a parameter to the constructor of this class

GetQualifiedName

public java.lang.String GetQualifiedName()
Get the qualified name of this table entry. The qualified name has the following format: . where is the name of the table template for this table entry is the value of a parameter "Name" of this table entry. If no such parameter exists then the name is set to "NoName".

MandatoryParametersValid

public boolean MandatoryParametersValid()
It checks whether all parameters which must always have a value are empty. If that is the case it returns "false" else it returns "true"

Returns:
True if all mandatory table parameters have values, else false
